FBIS4-37983 "drnes123_j_94040" FBIS-NES-94-123 Daily Report 24 Jun 1994 Arabian Peninsula Minister Says Recognition a `Matter of Time' Minister Says Recognition a `Matter of Time' EA2406220094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 2040 GMT 24 Jun 94 EA2406220094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 2040 GMT 24 Jun 94 Arabic BFN [Text] Brother 'Abdallah 'Abd-al-Majid al-Asnaj, foreign affairs minister of the Democratic Republic of Yemen, said recognizing the Democratic Republic of Yemen has become a matter of time, and was neither a difficult, nor an impossible matter. In an interview with the Lebanese AL-ANWAR, Brother 'Abdallah al-Asnaj expected that recognizing the Democratic Republic of Yemen could take place in a few days, not weeks. Brother al-Asnaj accused the rulers of Sanaa of waging a barbaric war against the southerners with the aim of occupying the south.
